{"type":"message","id":"c0890d4f","parentId":"25358f93","timestamp":"2026-04-22T06:08:56.988Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_nTSsg4zUviK5inAuuLUycA8V","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"name\": \"frontend\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"dev\": \"next dev\",\n    \"build\": \"next build\",\n    \"start\": \"next start\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint\",\n    \"test\": \"jest\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"chart.js\": \"^4.5.1\",\n    \"framer-motion\": \"^12.38.0\",\n    \"lucide-react\": \"^1.7.0\",\n    \"next\": \"16.2.2\",\n    \"react\": \"19.2.4\",\n    \"react-chartjs-2\": \"^5.3.1\",\n    \"react-dom\": \"19.2.4\",\n    \"sonner\": \"^2.0.7\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@tailwindcss/postcss\": \"^4\",\n    \"@testing-library/dom\": \"^10.4.1\",\n    \"@testing-library/jest-dom\": \"^6.9.1\",\n    \"@testing-library/react\": \"^16.3.2\",\n    \"@types/chart.js\": \"^4.0.1\",\n    \"@types/jest\": \"^30.0.0\",\n    \"@types/node\": \"^20\",\n    \"@types/react\": \"^19\",\n    \"@types/react-dom\": \"^19\",\n    \"dotenv-cli\": \"^8.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^9\",\n    \"eslint-config-next\": \"16.2.2\",\n    \"jest\": \"^30.3.0\",\n    \"jest-environment-jsdom\": \"^30.3.0\",\n    \"tailwindcss\": \"^4\",\n    \"ts-jest\": \"^29.4.9\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5\"\n  }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776838136981}}
{"type":"message","id":"112a402a","parentId":"c0890d4f","timestamp":"2026-04-22T06:08:56.996Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_EWbC0Hx4lyI1Go7j31G66kg9","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Driving Training Management System - Frontend\n\nThis is the frontend application for the Driving Training Management System, built with **Next.js**, **React**, and **Tailwind CSS**. It provides an intuitive, high-performance dashboard for managing students, courses, exam schedules, and tracking practice progress (DAT).\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 Technologies Used\n\n- **Framework**: [Next.js 14+](https://nextjs.org/) (App Directory)\n- **UI Library**: [React 18](https://react.dev/)\n- **Styling**: [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com/) & custom CSS patterns\n- **State Management**: React Context / Hooks\n- **Icons**: [Lucide React](https://lucide.dev/)\n- **Animation**: [Framer Motion](https://www.framer.com/motion/)\n- **API Communication**: `axios` with global interceptors\n- **Testing**: Jest & React Testing Library\n- **Linting & Formatting**: ESLint (Flat Config)\n\n---\n\n## 📂 Folder Structure\n\n```text\nfrontend/\n├── public/                 # Static assets (images, icons)\n├── src/\n│   ├── app/                # Next.js App Router (pages & layouts)\n│   ├── components/         # Reusable UI components\n│   │   ├── layout/         # Sidebar, Header, etc.\n│   │   ├── shared/         # Common UI elements (Modals, Spinners, Selects, etc.)\n│   │   └── [features]/     # Feature-specific components (students, courses, progress)\n│   ├── context/            # React Context providers (AuthContext, etc.)\n│   ├── hooks/              # Custom React hooks\n│   ├── lib/                # Utility libraries (axios config, formatters)\n│   ├── services/           # Backend API integration layers (studentService, authService)\n│   └── types/              # TypeScript interfaces and type definitions\n├── __tests__/              # Unit and Component tests\n├── .env.local              # Local environment variables\n└── eslint.config.mjs       # ESLint rules & overrides\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🛠️ Setup & Installation\n\n### Requirements\n- Node.js >= 20.x\n- Yarn >= 1.22.x\n- Backend server running (Ensure the `.env.local` API URL points to it).\n\n### 1. Install Dependencies\n\nYou **MUST** use `yarn` for package management (`npm` is strictly prohibited in this project).\n\n```bash\ncd frontend\nyarn install\n```\n\n### 2. Configure Environment\n\nCreate a `.env.local` or `.env` file in the `frontend` directory:\n\n```env\nNEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api/v1\n```\n\n### 3. Run Development Server\n\n```bash\nyarn dev\n```\n\nOpen [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) with your browser to see the result.\n\n---\n\n## 🧪 Testing and Linting\n\n- **Run Linter**: \n  ```bash\n  yarn lint\n  ```\n- **Run Tests**:\n  ```bash\n  yarn test\n  ```\n\n---\n\n## 🎨 UI/UX Philosophy\n\nThe frontend is designed with a premium look, leveraging robust glassmorphism effects, cinematic animations (Framer Motion), and responsive standard views. Strict component composition using Shadcn-like philosophies allows clean, maintainable presentation code.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776838136990}}
{"type":"message","id":"00b9cbdd","parentId":"112a402a","timestamp":"2026-04-22T06:08:57.003Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_h7y72CKqMocBloqKaPgm8AJR","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"name\": \"backend\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"\",\n  \"main\": \"index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"dev\": \"ts-node-dev -r tsconfig-paths/register src/index.ts\",\n    \"start\": \"node dist/src/index.js\",\n    \"build\": \"tsc && tsc-alias\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint 'src/**/*.ts' --no-warn-ignored\",\n    \"test\": \"jest\",\n    \"test:watch\": \"jest --watch\",\n    \"test:coverage\": \"jest --coverage\",\n    \"seed\": \"ts-node -r tsconfig-paths/register src/scripts/master_seeder.ts\",\n    \"seed:realistic\": \"ts-node -r tsconfig-paths/register src/scripts/realistic_seed.ts\",\n    \"seed:ultimate\": \"ts-node -r tsconfig-paths/register src/scripts/ultimate_seed.ts\",\n    \"seed:master\": \"ts-node -r tsconfig-paths/register src/scripts/master_seeder.ts\"\n  },\n  \"keywords\": [],\n  \"author\": \"\",\n  \"license\": \"ISC\",\n  \"type\": \"commonjs\",\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@types/helmet\": \"^0.0.48\",\n    \"bcrypt\": \"^6.0.0\",\n    \"cookie-parser\": \"^1.4.7\",\n    \"cors\": \"^2.8.6\",\n    \"dotenv\": \"^17.4.0\",\n    \"exceljs\": \"^4.4.0\",\n    \"express\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"express-rate-limit\": \"^8.3.2\",\n    \"firebase-admin\": \"^13.8.0\",\n    \"helmet\": \"^8.1.0\",\n    \"jsonwebtoken\": \"^9.0.3\",\n    \"mongoose\": \"^9.3.3\",\n    \"multer\": \"^2.1.1\",\n    \"swagger-ui-express\": \"^5.0.1\",\n    \"twilio\": \"^5.13.1\",\n    \"winston\": \"^3.19.0\",\n    \"xlsx\": \"^0.18.5\",\n    \"xss\": \"^1.0.15\",\n    \"zod\": \"^4.3.6\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@eslint/js\": \"^10.0.1\",\n    \"@faker-js/faker\": \"^10.4.0\",\n    \"@types/bcrypt\": \"^6.0.0\",\n    \"@types/cookie-parser\": \"^1.4.10\",\n    \"@types/cors\": \"^2.8.19\",\n    \"@types/express\": \"^5.0.6\",\n    \"@types/jest\": \"^30.0.0\",\n    \"@types/jsonwebtoken\": \"^9.0.10\",\n    \"@types/mongoose\": \"^5.11.96\",\n    \"@types/multer\": \"^2.1.0\",\n    \"@types/node\": \"^25.5.0\",\n    \"@types/supertest\": \"^7.2.0\",\n    \"@types/swagger-ui-express\": \"^4.1.8\",\n    \"@types/twilio\": \"^3.19.3\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^10.1.0\",\n    \"jest\": \"^30.3.0\",\n    \"mongodb-memory-server\": \"^11.0.1\",\n    \"prettier\": \"^3.8.1\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.2.2\",\n    \"ts-jest\": \"^29.4.9\",\n    \"ts-node-dev\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"tsc-alias\": \"^1.8.16\",\n    \"tsconfig-paths\": \"^4.2.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^6.0.2\",\n    \"typescript-eslint\": \"^8.58.0\"\n  }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776838136996}}
{"type":"message","id":"472db9c4","parentId":"00b9cbdd","timestamp":"2026-04-22T06:08:57.009Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ekqyMuHQqNjCadc40JOPpxS3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Driving Training Management System - Backend\n\nThis is the robust, high-performance Node.js backend infrastructure running the Driving Training Management System API.\n\n---\n\n## 🏗 Architecture & Design\n\nThe backend strictly conforms to **Clean Architecture** patterns, ensuring a resilient separation of concerns.\n\n- **`domain/`**: Enterprise logic, business rules, models, and robust abstractions. Independent of any frameworks.\n- **`application/`**: Use cases and application-specific logic (`services/`).\n- **`interface/`**: Presentation layer handling HTTP connections (`controllers/`, `routes/`, `middlewares/`).\n- **`infrastructure/`**: Database implementations (`repositories/`), caching, sockets, and heavy integrations.\n\n---\n\n## 🛠 Technology Stack\n\n- **Runtime**: [Node.js 20+](https://nodejs.org/)\n- **Framework**: [Express.js](https://expressjs.com/)\n- **Language**: TypeScript (Strict Typing enforced)\n- **Database**: [MongoDB](https://www.mongodb.com/) via [Mongoose](https://mongoosejs.com/)\n- **State/Caching**: Node `node-cache`\n- **Real-time Engine**: [Socket.io](https://socket.io/)\n- **Validation**: [Joi](https://joi.dev/)\n- **Logging**: [Winston](https://github.com/winstonjs/winston) (Mandatory system wide logs, NO `console.log`)\n- **Package Manager**: [Yarn](https://yarnpkg.com/)\n\n---\n\n## 📁 Directory Layout\n\n```text\nbackend/\n├── src/\n│   ├── application/       # Service layer (Student, Auth, Payment)\n│   ├── domain/            # Entities and domain exceptions\n│   ├── infrastructure/    # Mongoose Models, DB Connections, WebSockets\n│   ├── interface/         # Express Controllers, Routes, and request Middlewares\n│   └── index.ts           # Application entry point/Bootstrapper\n├── tests/                 # Unit & End-to-End tests\n├── .env.example           # Example Secrets\n├── eslint.config.cjs      # ESLint strict guidelines\n└── tsconfig.json          # TypeScript definitions\n```\n\n---\n\n## ⚙️ Configuration & Execution\n\n### Requirements\n- Node.js >= 20.x\n- Yarn >= 1.22.x\n- MongoDB (Local instance or Atlas cluster)\n\n### 1. Install Dependencies\nYou **MUST** use `yarn` for installation to avoid lockfile conflicts.\n\n```bash\ncd backend\nyarn install\n```\n\n### 2. Environment Variables\n\nCopy `.env.example` to `.env` and fill the variables:\n\n```env\nPORT=5000\nMONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/ahv-system\nJWT_SECRET=super_secret_string\nJWT_EXPIRES_IN=24h\nNODE_ENV=development\n```\n\n### 3. Run the Server\n\n```bash\n# Start in development mode (nodemon + ts-node)\nyarn dev\n\n# Compile safely for production environments\nyarn build\n\n# Run production compiled application\nyarn start\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🛡️ Coding Standards (Strict Workflow)\n\n1. **Never use `console.log`**. Instead, import your logger instance and utilise `logger.info()`, `logger.error()`, etc.\n2. **Never wrap controllers in manual `try/catch`**. All controllers must be wrapped using the `catchAsync` architectural middleware.\n3. **Consistent Error Envelope**. The system returns strict `{ success: boolean, data/message: any }` schemas.\n4. **No Static Methods**. Classes must use instance methods (no `static` methods).\n\n---\n\n## 🧪 Testing\n\n```bash\n# Run linting\nyarn lint\n\n# Execute Unit Tests\nyarn test\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776838137003}}
